message.content:
cs.SC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.LO

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new open-source library for the reconstruction of multivariate rational functions over finite fields, which involves symbolic computation techniques.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the library can be used in the context of integration-by-parts reductions, which is a common problem in control theory.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses the algorithms used in the implementation of the library.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as the library may have applications in geometric modeling and computer graphics.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possibility as the paper may involve some logical reasoning in the development of the library and the algorithms used.
